channel.title: Re-Starting Runescape
channel.description:
Alright, well im starting too play rs again. Only problem is, my character is broke. I gave all my stuff away, im stuck with 230k :\
My character name is Atk2-99, you can hs him for my stats. How should i get back on track? I used to be pretty rich from fishing, but i got rid of it all, and i dont wanna start runescape with a solid 2 weeks of fishing.. Cause then ill loose interest again..
Any tips?

[/quote]I hope you realize that Moparisthebest is highly against scammers. So, I’d watch what you said, or you shouldn’t be surprised if he were to ban you.

No one cares, calm down. lol.[/quote]

[quote=“the elve age, post:13, topic:401317”][quote author=T4_ link=topic=498379.msg3644877#msg3644877 date=1309301570]

Start botting. You won’t get banned unless you 24/7 it.

Not exactly true. It’s mainly based on whether or not you’re reported and the number of reports OR if there was an update that breaks a certain functionality of the bot and/or script that is obvious which Jagex would use to identify botters.
[/quote]
Don’t use a shitty bot then.[/quote]
Mostly true, but as for updates by Jagex that breaks functionality (without the user noticing immediately) is somewhat unavoidable.

item.title: Re-Starting Runescape
item.dc:creator: @Andrew_Ferguson The317Guy
item.description:
@Andrew_Ferguson wrote:

Fridder:

RuneScape sucks, don’t go back to it.

This is the RuneScape Discussion section, if you hate the game the get the fuck out and stop posting things pointlessly.

the elve age:

Start botting. You won’t get banned unless you 24/7 it.

Learn the facts before you post because that is not true at all.

OT: The best thing to do in RuneScape for money will probably always be skills due to the steady income, but you can always join a skilling clan to make it more enjoyable, some clans even have weekly give-aways to their members. I must say though, if your looking to play RuneScape for fun don’t bot, it will take away the point of the game and it really is a high risk these days.
